China Railway, Shenhua, Hunan Valin: China Equity Preview

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-07-11T17:09:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/china-railway-shenhua-hunan-valin-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 0.2 percent to 2,802.69. The  CSI
300 Index (SHSZ300)  rose 0.1 percent to 3,113.21.  China Railway Construction Corp. (601186 CH): The
construction company won 8.51 billion yuan ($1.3 billion) of
contracts in Kunming, Xinjiang and Hubei, it said in a Shanghai
Stock Exchange filing yesterday. The stock closed unchanged at
5.95 yuan.  China Shenhua Energy Co. (601088 CH): The Chinese coal and
power company agreed to form a joint venture to produce and sell
power with Anhui Province Energy, it said in a statement
yesterday. Shares fell 1.7 percent to 30.89 yuan.  Hunan Valin Steel Co. (000932 CH): The steel company said
its first-half net loss may be between 198 million yuan and 238
million yuan, according to a statement to the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange yesterday. The stock fell 1.2 percent to 4.05 yuan.  Jiangxi Copper Co. (600362 CH):  China ’s biggest copper
producer set up a trading company to expand domestic and
international sales, Reuters reported yesterday, citing Pan Qifang, a Jiangxi spokesman.  The venture now trades copper and zinc with plans to expand
to other base metals, the report said, citing an unidentified
person. The shares 0.8 percent lower at 35.96 yuan.  --Zhang Shidong, Liza Lin. Editor: Brendan Walsh, Marie-France Han  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
